	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><date>October 13th 1863</date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>San Francisco California</placeName></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">I suppose<lb/> you are <sic>surprized</sic> I did not write to you for<lb/> so long.  I have nothing of much interest to<lb/> you.  Enclosed I send you some items&#44; which<lb/> probably you may be disposed to notice in<lb/> your Journal.  I have only stated facts<lb/> up to the present I have not yet received<lb/> the parcel you sent me it has been mislaid<lb/> but they have promised to look for it and<lb/> send it to me&#44; and then I will acknowledge<lb/> it.  Your Books I find hard to sell.  One<lb/> <sic>sett</sic> I have sold.  I will collect the money<lb/> and send it to you shortly as also some from<lb/> myself.  I think I could sell 2 <sic>setts</sic> of<lb/> your <sic>portuguese</sic> <add>Hebrew</add> complete if<lb/> you have them the Octavo Edition send<lb/> me the lowest price&#44; and let the freight be<lb/> small as the people grudge to pay the<lb/> same.  I send you enclosed a prospectus<lb/> of my proposed little work which I intend<lb/> shortly to publish and then will send some<lb/> copies to you by opportunities which may often<lb/> be same expense..possibly you can dispose</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>of some of them.  My plan is to secure<lb/> sufficient subscribers to pay the expense<lb/> so that I have no outlay&#8212;altho&#39; it is<lb/> attended with some trouble.  I am much<lb/> pleased with your rejoinder to <persName>Mr De<lb/> Solla</persName> in the interment question.  He must<lb/> be a great <add>Hebrew</add>.  I should feel greatly<lb/> obliged to you to send me his pamphlet<lb/> and the <persName>Revd Mr Nathans</persName> reply on the<lb/> subject of the <add>Hebrew</add> married by him<lb/> some time ago.  You can send it through<lb/> the post and I will pay the cost</p>
				<p>Do you know that <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> is engaged<lb/> at <placeName>St Thomas&#39;</placeName> in the place of <persName>Mr<lb/> Myers</persName> late of <placeName>London</placeName> who is now at<lb/> <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>&#44; <hi rend="underline">entre vous</hi>.  He is<lb/> a real charlatan.  I know him from<lb/> childhood&#8212;what a pity that congregations<lb/> are not more particular in engaging them<lb/> as ministers&#33;  We hear nothing in this Region<lb/> of <persName>Wise</persName> and <persName>Lilienthal</persName>&#8212;I suppose you<lb/> do.  How goes the War&#63;  I hope you were<lb/> in health to perform your duties on the late<lb/> Holy days&#8212;let me hear from you soon<lb/> I am always pleased to read your letters<lb/> Trusting this will reach in health and<lb/> happiness&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Believe me</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName></p>
		</body>
